1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Build a Bluetooth remote for your micro:bit —
no code required.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Drag a Button. Drop a Joystick. Done.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Twelve widgets — Buttons, Sliders,
D-Pad, XY Pad, Gauge, Graph.

4
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Open the Code tab —
your MakeCode is already written.

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Play tab, pair over BLE, press a button —
the micro:bit reacts.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Six tabs: Build, Play, Demo,
Export, Import, Code. That is it.

7
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:55,000
Link below — lifetime updates,
teachers and kids welcome.

8
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Build. Pair. Play.
